name: Miracle House
notes:
The specific purpose for Coast Valley’s sober living environments are to provide a setting in which individuals beset with substance abuse problems can make the necessary changes in their lives and grow spiritually. Miracle is a quasi-residential program. Residents Attend Treatment at Coast Valley’s F st location in Lompoc. Resident’s engage in house meetings, prayer time, meditation, and Cognitive Behavioral groups each week. Resident’s are randomly tested for Alcohol and Drugs. Rent is $600/mo.This includes room, board, utilities, internet, cable, Netflix, and food.

Cost: $640/month and $DEPOSIT

notes: Immigrant Hope – Santa Barbara offers honest, low-cost legal advice & services regarding the U.S. immigration processes in a safe and caring environment.  We have a staff of accredited representatives and volunteers that will meet with you to understand your situation. We will help you understand your options and, if able, carefully guide you through the process you are applying for.  Consultations cost $30; if we are able to take your case, the cost of the consultation is applied to your case fee.  All case information is confidential.  Immigrant Hope-Santa Barbara is a 501(c)(3) non-profit organization and is Recognized by the Department of Justice (DOJ) to offer immigration legal services.

name: North County Crisis Services
notes: To obtain support for someone experiencing a mental health crisis: There are three possibilities: (1) If the crisis places anyone in immediate danger, call 911. (2) If the crisis does not involve immediate danger, and if the person in crisis has insurance coverage through a health plan, call the health plan to get a referral to a covered mental health provider. (3) For all others, call ACCESS Line at 1(888) 868-1649. The call is toll-free, and someone will answer to assist you 24 hours per day, seven days a week.
